COPYING.provenance — per-file porting provenance for @session.js/calls
========================================================================

License decision (plan D10): everything shipped in this package is licensed
AGPL-3.0-or-later. Official Session clients are GPLv3 (session-android,
session-ios) and AGPLv3 (session-desktop). GPLv3 code combines into an
AGPLv3 work per AGPLv3 §13. All upstream copyright notices are preserved in
the headers of ported files, and changes are annotated ("modified"), as GPL
requires. © of ported portions: Session Foundation.

PORTED FILES
------------

src/fsm/state-machine.ts
  Ported from session-android
  `app/src/main/java/org/thoughtcrime/securesms/webrtc/data/StateMachine.kt`
  (GPLv3), © Session Foundation, modified (Kotlin → TypeScript table-driven
  port; two documented supplementary rows added for the caller-side
  local-pre-offer ambiguity — see the in-file comment and
  docs/evidence/P2-T1.md). Licensed under AGPL-3.0-or-later.

src/supervisor.ts
  Gating/dispatch logic ported from session-android
  `org/session/libsession/messaging/calls/CallMessageProcessor.kt` (GPLv3)
  and session-desktop `ts/receiver/callMessage.ts` (AGPLv3), © Session
  Foundation, modified (adapted to structural SessionLike/SignalingSender/
  MediaEngine interfaces; single-device headless operation). Licensed under
  AGPL-3.0-or-later.

FRESH-WRITTEN FILES
-------------------

src/types.ts        — written fresh (normative §4.3 API surface). SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
src/errors.ts       — written fresh (P6-T3 error taxonomy). SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
src/policy.ts       — written fresh (freshness windows from §3.1/§3.2 facts;
                      TURN constants are the public values shipped in every
                      official Session client, Appendix B). SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
src/index.ts        — written fresh (barrel). SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
test/**             — written fresh. SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.

Scaffolded for later phases (not yet implemented):

src/media/          — reserved for the media plane (werift PeerConnectionManager,
                      AudioBridge, SDP munging; will port Android
                      PeerConnectionWrapper.kt (GPLv3) and session-desktop
                      CallManager.ts (AGPLv3), © Session Foundation, modified).

